{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "After removing duplicate film entries (using title and production year), we only included festivals with at least 15 unique films in their programming.",
    "Although we base it on policy guidelines [3], this is an arbitrary threshold that balances between including smaller festivals and partial entries and leaving enough data to construct reasonably reliable festival profiles and distributions.",
    "When deduplicating films within festivals, we rank them by the number of tags in the target metadata variable (e.g.",
    "production countries) and the presence of production year, keeping the most informative entries.",
    "After cleaning, merging, and applying this threshold, 31,989 unique films spread across 616 festivals are left (including 28 one-off events and 588 events belonging to 102 identifiable festival series (i.e. 2 or more events))."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
